combined_text: Title: Pluto contract number is not coming in ZSD204 in multiple lines of 120 BA | Description: | Category: SAP-GT-ECC-Support | Subcategory: Sales & Distribution | Comments and Work Notes: 2025-02-11 10:52:10 - Muthu Mano (Work notes) ***capturing log for effort tracking fields action=resolve_incident contact=self-service assign_grp=5fda20cc0f2854109f3f05ace1050ee2 fld NOT empty devlop= config= doc= cust_int= testing= supp_func=0 06:00:00 tech_trbl=0 02:00:00 coord= tot=8.00 2025-02-11 10:52:08 - Muthu Mano (Additional comments) [code]KB0012499 : No KB Article[/code] 2025-02-10 17:55:51 - Muthu Mano (Additional comments) Dear Timmanna, In ZSD204 report, Pluto contract number field is filling based on the value available in the reference sales order number. Normally, if the sales order is created in ZSD9002 T-code, these values will be captured in the sales order. Except one invoice, all other invoice you shared are credit return, credit note, and debit note. These invoice's references are created under VA01 t-code. So, the Pluto contract numbers are not available in the reference orders. The sales invoice which you shared has three different PO contract numbers in the sales order. Please check from your end and confirm us whether it was clubbed. Please reach us if you have any questions. Regards Muthu Mano. 2025-02-08 13:50:12 - Muthu Mano (Additional comments) Dear Timmanna, In ZSD204 report, Pluto contract number field is filling based on the value available in the reference sales order number. Normally, if the sales order is created in ZSD9002 T-code, these values will be captured in the sales order. Except one invoice, all other invoice you shared are credit return, credit note, and debit note. These invoice's references are created under VA01 t-code. So, the Pluto contract numbers are not available in the reference orders. The sales invoice which you shared has three different PO contract numbers in the sales order. Please check from your end and confirm us whether it was clubbed. Please reach us if you have any questions. Regards Muthu Mano. 2025-02-05 18:18:43 - Muthu Mano (Work notes) This Incident has been converted from the Request - RITM1563270
resolution_notes:
Dear Timmanna,
In ZSD204 report, Pluto contract number field is filling based on the value available in the reference sales order number. Normally, if the sales order is created in ZSD9002 T-code, these values will be captured in the sales order. Except one invoice, all other invoice you shared are credit return, credit note, and debit note. These invoice's references are created under VA01 t-code. So, the Pluto contract numbers are not available in the reference orders.

The sales invoice which you shared has three different PO contract numbers in the sales order. Please check from your end and confirm us whether it was clubbed. Please reach us if you have any questions.

Regards
Muthu Mano.
